commit.message: test new grepdiff `--only-match` option

grepdiff: add `--only-match` option

This option allows to only apply regex filtering on removals, additions,
modifications, or the whole hunk.

Closes #3

tests: use `printf` instead of `echo -ne`

On some systems (like macOS), `/bin/echo` does not take the `-e` flag.
Moreover, echo flags are undefined in POSIX sh [1].

[1] https://unix.stackexchange.com/tags/echo/info

Allow more 3 lines in headers

Fix for https://github.com/twaugh/patchutils/issues/14

For some reason MAX_HEADERS is 6 so let's have 6 lines in the headers as
defined in variable MAX_HEADERS

Fix hunk trimming

Fixes #34.

commit.message:
filterdiff: always use string literal format strings

The result of regerror() was being passed directly to error() as
a format string, causing build-time failures with strict
checking.

Signed-off-by: Tim Waugh <twaugh@redhat.com>
fixes from review (#13)

filterdiff: Fix header output.

When outputting header lines, apply prefix changes only to lines
starting with "---" and "+++" but also apply these changes to
arguments of a possibly diff command line.

Adapt tests/fullheader4/run-test and remove it from XFAIL_TESTS.

This fixes #12.
Add test to show failure described in #12

filterdiff: Display hunk comments containing NUL

If the comment for a hunk contains an ASCII NUL, then no newline would be
output before the first line of context (as the c-string 'ended'
prematurely).  This breaks the patch such that it cannot be applied, even
with a fuzz factor.  Handle this unorthodox case to better support binary
files.

Add test to show failure caused by NUL

The presense of an ASCII NUL in the hunk comment causes filterdiff to break the
diff.  Create a simplified test case to illustrate this error found in the wild.
